<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-054-024 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 314 309</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Sept 24 1991 v5 n32 p12(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Calera Systems spells faster OCR; RISC chips offer 1,000 percentboost. (Calera Recognition Systems Inc.'s reduced-instruction-setcomputing optical character recognition scanning systems) (briefarticle) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rothenberg, Matthew.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Calera Recognition Systems Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Calera Recognition Systems MX2400 (Scanning device) (Productintroduction)Calera Recognition Systems MM2400 (Scanning device) (Productintroduction)Calera Recognition Systems MM600 (Scanning device) (Productintroduction)Calera Recognition Systems MX600 (Scanning device) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionOptical Character ReadersScanning DevicesReduced-Instruction-Set Computers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>RISC chips offer 1,000 percent boostandM;By Matthew RothenbergandM;Sunnyvale, Calif.andP;  -- Calera Recognition Systems Inc. last week announced aline of RISC (reduced instruction set computing)-based systems that thecompany said are up to 1,000 percent faster than any previous opticalcharacter recognition solution.andM;The new M/Series, which connects to the Mac via SCSI and runs Calera'sTopScan Mac software, includes:andM;andgt;MX2400.andP;  Due this month, the $44,995 OCR system includes a recognitiondevice with four NuBus cards and a 300-dpi scanner equipped with an automaticdocument feeder that can handle up to 80 pages.andP;  The MX2400 can process up to28,000 words per minute, according to Calera.andM;andgt;MX600.andP;  Available now for $39,495, the system includes a single-cardrecognition device and the same scanner as the MX2400.andP;  The MX600, which canscan up to 7,000 words per minute, can be upgraded to the MX2400 for $24,995.andM;andgt;MM2400 and MM600.andP;  The $29,995 MM2400 and $24,495 MM600 ship withoutscanners but support third-party devices, including the Fujitsu 3093 and 3096and Hewlett-Packard Co.'s ScanJet series, Calera said.andP;  Through Dec.andP;  31,owners of Calera's CDP 6000 and 900 OCR systems can upgrade to either theMM2400 or MM600; upgrade prices vary with model and age of the CDP.andM;Calera also offers a $995 Software Developer's Kit.andM;Calera Recognitions Systems Inc. is at 475 Potrero Ave., Sunnyvale, Calif.andO;94086.andP;  Phone (408) 720-8300; fax (408) 720-1330.andO;</TEXT></DOC>